                    <p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Career in Argentina</strong></p>
                    <p> < strong>"Argentinos Juniors" </strong></p>
                    <p><strong>1976</strong></p>
                    On October 20, 1976, 10 days before his 16th birthday, Maradona made his debut in the main squad of Argentinos Juniors, coming 10 minutes before the end of the match at number 16 in the match of the championship of Argentina. Despite the fact that the "Red bugs" lost the match club "Talleres", Maradona immediately showed itself, making several passes and also set up a goal, not implemented Jorge Lopez, after which the defender "Talleres" Juan Cabrera was charged with coaching benches personally to take care of a 16-year-old footballer. On the evening after the match, Maradona said: "On this day, I touched the sky with my hands." After the game, Maradona received even a small fee, but the biggest reward was the respect of the fans, as well as press reviews:<br>Maradona, a young player who will turn sixteen in ten days, stepped up his attack at the end of the match. His ability to control the ball stands out even against the background of the players from Cordoba, who are rightly considered the best "techies" in Argentine football. However, even this dodger failed to ram the iron defense of the "Talleres", and "Argentinos" was forced to concede 0: 1.</p>
                    <p>In the next game with the club "Newells Old Boys" Maradona was in the starting line-up. However, the match was unsuccessful for both Maradona and the club, who lost 2:4. After that, the young player was sent to play for the second team of Juniors for several months. Only on November 14, he again appeared on the field in the match of the foundation with the club "San Lorenzo", replacing Giacobetti at the end of the second half. And here Maradona showed his talent, scoring two goals in a short time. After this match, Diego has already become the basis player of the "Red Beetles", having played 11 matches and scored 2 goals. The press spoke positively about the young footballer's game, but he himself said that he still has a lot to learn.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p>
                         <strong>1977 and 1978</strong>
                    </p>
                    <p>In 1977, Cesar Luis Menotti, the head coach of the Argentine national team, called Maradona to a friendly match with the Hungarian national team, held on February 27. Maradona came on 20 minutes before the end of the match, replacing Leopoldo Luque, but did not show anything special. Diego himself was dissatisfied with his performance in this match. The challenge was unexpected: by that time, Maradona had played only 12 games for the Juniors ' main squad.
                    <p>In February (when I was sixteen years old) I made my debut for the national team in a game at the familiar Boca Juniors stadium against the Hungarian national team. I was invited by Menotti himself. He called me on the phone: "Maradona, Maradona, is that you? — What is it? " he asked twice. — I included you in the squad for the game with the Hungarians. Are you coming?"» Menotti was being sly when he asked that question. He knew that if he called any Argentine football player to the national team, he would immediately rush to the training camp.</p>
                    <p>On April 3 of the same year, Maradona made his debut with the youth national team of Argentina, with which he played at the youth Championship of South America, held in the same year in Venezuela. There, Diego played all 3 matches of the national team. For the Red Beetles, Maradona also had a good season, playing in 49 games and scoring 19 goals. Leading South American and European clubs began to "hunt" for the young Argentine talent, but Diego refused everyone, preferring to prepare for the World Cup in a calm atmosphere, for a trip where Maradona was one of the candidates.</p>
                    <p>But Diego did not go to the World Cup: 13 days before the start of the tournament, he became the last excluded from the preliminary application of the national team. The announcement sent young Diego into a fit of hysteria. Three days later, he even called Menotti at home and begged him to let him go to the World Cup, but he refused. Maradona said:</p><blockquote>
                         <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; "It was the biggest upset in my life. Being in great shape, burning with the desire to play for your team and be out of work-you can't survive this."</p>
                    </blockquote>
                    <p>I never forgave Menotti and I never will — I still think he missed his chance — but I never hated him. Hating is not the same as not forgiving. It was terrible at home. It was like a funeral. My mother was crying, my father was crying, my brothers and sisters were crying. They told me that I was the best, that I had nothing to worry about, because I would have time to play in five more championships. But they were all crying. And that was the worst part. On that saddest day of my career, I swore I would take it. With my feet, my heart, and my thoughts, I felt that I would show them all again. I will play in many more world championships.</p>
                    <p>A possible reason for not inviting Maradona to the tournament was that Menotti did not like his extremely explosive nature. The head coach called him a "savage" and accused him of giving interviews only for money, on the advice of his impresario. Another reason was that the team leader Daniel Passarella did not want to see young players in the squad, and especially Diego. Returning to Argentinos from the national team, Maradona played a match with the club "Chacarita Juniors", where he scored 2 goals and made 2 assists; his club won the match 5-0. In total, Maradona scored 25 goals in 35 matches, including 22 goals in Metropolitano, becoming the top scorer of the championship. After the World Cup, where Argentina won its first ever title, Menotti called up several players of the youth team to the camp of the main Argentine team, among whom was Maradona. In the National Championship of Argentina, Maradona played 4 games and scored 4 goals in them.<p>&nbsp;</p>
