                    <p>With Boka, Maradona signed one of the most financially lucrative contracts in Argentine football — he was paid 15 salaries of 60 thousand dollars a year, as well as 10 thousand for each exhibition match. The club also insured Diego-in the event of an injury, Boca would have received 500 thousand dollars. This transition changed not only the life of the football player, but also the life of his family, who moved to a new spacious house. On the day of signing the contract, Diego played in a friendly match between Argentinos Juniors and Boca Juniors, playing in each team's half and scoring a goal for Boca from the penalty spot.</p>
                    <p>The official debut of Maradona in the "Genoese" took place on February 22. In the match against Boca's rival, Talleres, Maradona's club won 4-1, and Diego himself scored 2 goals. At the same time, he left the game with an injury that he received while playing for Argentinos Juniors: he had sore muscles in his right leg. Despite the pain, Diego continued to play for the club until March 8, when he was found to have a tear in the muscle tissue of his thigh, due to which he had to withdraw from playing until March 29. On April 10, a few days after recovering from his injury, Maradona played in his first Superclasico, a classic match between Boka and River Plate. The game was played at the Bombonera; Boquita won 3-0, and Maradona scored one of his team's 3 goals (the other two were scored by Brindisi), beating Fillol and Tarantini.</p>
                    <p>In the same 1981, Maradona had a conflict with the head coach Silvio Marsolini, who did not give the freedom in the game that the forward had in "Argentinos". In addition, Marsolini was a very demanding mentor in everything related to discipline and training, which Diego did not like. According to Maradona, Marsolini was afraid that Diego could get out of control. In addition, the team suffered from the fan group "12", which, after 4 consecutive games without a win, broke into the team's base with a weapon, demanding better results.</p>
                    <p>Maradona won the Metropolitano tournament with Boca, drawing 1-1 with Racing in the last round; Diego scored the goal in this game, after converting a penalty. After the game with River Plate, the main rival of the "Genoese" secretly offered Maradona a super-profitable contract, but he refused. Boca's tournament National was unsuccessful: the club lost in the 1/4 final to Velez Sarsfield, while Maradona was sent off in the first game with this team, and did not participate in the second due to disqualification caused by the removal. The match against Velez was Maradona's last for Boca in the Argentine league during his first stint at the club. The loss was attributed to the large number of friendly matches played by the team, which Boca was forced to play due to the club's unsatisfactory financial situation. After one of the defeats, Pablo Abbatangelo, a member of the club's board of directors, came into the locker room of Boca, he hinted that the players do not fully give their best on the football field. To this, Diego, on the air of the TV program "60 minutes", called Abbatangelo a fool. In the national team, Diego played some good matches in Europe and South America, but a little later, due to too tight a schedule of games, he missed several training sessions, and Menotti dropped him from the team. After a negative assessment of this event in the press, the football player and the coach reconciled, although they did not communicate anywhere else except on the field.</p>
                    <p>In the winter of 1982, Maradona played his last games for Boquita at the Verano tournament, as he had to concentrate on preparing for the World Cup in Spain. The last match in the "Boca Juniors" football player played on February 6, 1982 with "River Plate", and in it "Boca" was defeated. In total, he played 40 matches for the club and scored 28 goals.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p><strong>World Cup 1982</strong></p>
                    <p>Argentina's preparation for the World Cup took 4 months. The whole of Argentina, inspired by the victory of the national team at the last World Cup and the success of the youth team in 1979, demanded that the team win. The championship for Argentina started on June 13 in a match against Belgium; in this game, the Argentines were defeated with a score of 0: 1. This match was the first for Diego at the World Championships. In it, he hit the crossbar with a free kick. In the second game, Argentina beat Hungary 4-1; Maradona was the best on the field and scored twice, in the 28th and 57th minutes. In Game 3, Argentina beat El Salvador 2-0 and advanced to the second round from 2nd place.</p>
                    <p>The second round also consisted of a group stage, in which there were 12 teams that made up 4 groups, the winners of the groups went to the semifinals, the remaining teams finished their performances. Argentina was placed in Group 3, along with Italy and Brazil. In the first match of the second group tournament, Argentina met with Italy and lost 1:2. Against Maradona, Claudio Gentile personally acted, coping with the guardianship of the Argentine, except for the case when Diego hit the crossbar. According to some experts, the main referee of the match should have removed Claudio, who acted very harshly with the Argentine, who insulted the defender throughout the game: "Maradona insulted me, my mother and generally told me everything." In the second match, Argentina lost to Brazil 1: 3, and Maradona, who was the most active member of the "Albicelesta", was removed in the 85th minute from the field after hitting Batista. Thus, Argentina did not meet the expectations placed on it before the tournament.</p>
                    <p>One of the reasons for the poor performance is the close attention from the defenders, who played hard and sometimes rough against Diego. It was because of this that Maradona was sent off in the last game against Brazil, when he hit Batista, who violated the rules against him. According to Diego, the reason for the poor performance of the team was the poor physical preparation of the national team, which was very intense, as a result, the Argentine players came to the tournament very tired.</p>
                    <p>He was beaten so badly that I was afraid he would be killed altogether. In Spain, Maradona was already a star, and against every star they always play very carefully, hard, sometimes rough. Maybe he didn't have the experience then. It was his first time competing at a World Championship. And, of course, I did not expect that they would play so evil against him, and psychologically I was not ready for this. The Italians were especially tough on him, and their player Gentile played against Maradona just brutally. Rinat Dasaev about Maradona at the World Championship in 1982.</p>
