                    <p>In 1982, Maradona moved to the Catalan "Barcelona", which paid Diego himself 3 million dollars of "lifting" and 200 thousand dollars a year as a salary; the contract was signed for 6 years. The transfer amount was 1.2 billion pesetas ($8 million), with 66% of this amount going to Argentinos Juniors and the rest to Boke Juniors. This transfer was the most expensive in the history of football at that time.</p>
                    <p>Catalonia welcomed Maradona as a real football star: all the newspapers published a report on the arrival of Diego on the front pages. His debut game was a match on 4 September 1982 against Valencia, in which Barca lost 1:2. After the first matches, the player became a real idol of the Spanish public, and often local commentators, describing the successful individual actions of the players, said: "he played like Maradona." He made 15 appearances in the Spanish league and scored 6 goals before being diagnosed with hepatitis in December. Because of this disease, Maradona was left without football for 3 months. Without Maradona, Barcelona played 14 league games and several Cup games, where they were eliminated in the 1/4 finals.</p>
                    <p>On March 12, 1983, Maradona returned to the field in a match against Betis. In this match, Barcelona were led for the first time by the new head coach of Barcelona and Maradona's former mentor in the national team of Argentina, Cesar Luis Menotti. His arrival on the coaching bridge of the "blue-garnet" Diego supported: the former head coach of the club, Udo Lattek, was engaged in training exclusively running endurance exercises, which did not like Maradona at all. In the second game after his return, Diego scored three goals against Las Palmas. Shortly after the recovery of Maradona and the appointment of Menotti as head coach of Barcelona, the club achieved victory in the Spanish Cup. In his first season in Europe, Maradona made 35 appearances and scored 23 goals. In the championship, Barca finished fourth. In the same season, Diego helped his club win the Spanish League Cup, where he scored a goal in each of the two matches against the opponent, Real Madrid»; at the same time, the goal scored at the Santiago Bernabeu caused an ovation from the fans of Real Madrid, who appreciated the beauty of the moment when Maradona, having beaten two defenders and a goalkeeper, paused, as a result of which the defender of the "Royal Club" crashed into the post, and only after that scored a goal.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p><strong>1983/1984</strong></p>
                    <p>The 1983/1984 season started poorly for Maradona. On September 24, 1983, Barcelona met in the 4th round of the Spanish championship with Athletic club; in this game, which Barca won 4-0, the player received a very serious injury: Athletic player Andoni Goicoechea, who had been hitting Diego on the legs for the entire match, broke his ankle in the 59th minute of the match and caused a number of minor injuries. Because of this episode, a fight broke out on the field, in which all the representatives of the teams took part. Maradona was operated on in the Barcelona clinic by Dr. Gonzalez Adrio, who said that Diego will be able to return to the field only after 6 months. Diego then underwent a period of rehabilitation with a sports medic, Ruben Dario Oliva. Thanks to the course of treatment of this doctor, on January 8, 1984, in a match with Sevilla, Maradona returned to the field, and, making two assists, helped his club win 3-1. Despite the successful return, after several unimpressive matches, the audience, who remembered the game before the injury, began to boo him, in response to this, Diego shook his fist at her, which was very much not liked by the fans of the "blue-garnet". In total, in the 1983/1984 season, Diego played 23 matches and scored 15 goals, and Barcelona took only 3rd place in the championship.</p>
                    <p>Barca also reached the final of the Spanish Cup, where they faced Athletic, who became the champion of Spain, with Goicoechea in the squad, and lost 0: 1. Immediately after the game, Maradona attacked Athletic player Sola with his fists, as a result, a fight broke out on the field with the participation of almost all the players of the teams. After the game, several players of both clubs were disqualified, Maradona as one of the instigators of the fight was disqualified for 3 months.</p>
                    <p>In addition to Maradona's football performances, the press paid a lot of attention to his salary and behavior outside of football. In addition, the president of the team, Josep Nunes, criticized his player for frequent visits to nightclubs, which made Diego very angry. On one occasion, Nunes even took Maradona's passport to prevent him from going to Paul Breitner's farewell match. Diego's passport was returned only when he came to the club's office, where he made a scandal and broke the Teresa Herrera Cup. But Maradona was not released for Breitner's farewell match. Due to all these circumstances, injuries, illnesses and misunderstanding with Nunes, Maradona, after consulting with his common-law wife Claudia, decided to leave Barcelona. Diego was even willing to buy out his contract from the club. Soon the Catalan team received an offer from Italy: the club "Napoli" offered to buy the transfer of the player.</p>
                    <p>In just two seasons at Barcelona, Maradona made 58 appearances and scored 38 goals. In 1999, in honor of the centenary of Barca, a poll among fans was conducted on Catalan television, according to which Maradona is the third player in the history of the club; he was beaten only by Ladislav Kubala and Johan Cruyff. Despite a generally good performance in the blue-garnet squad, Maradona later said that the move to Barcelona was a mistake.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
