                    <p>
                         On June 29, 1984, former football player and then manager of the club "Napoli" Antonio Iuliano began negotiations with" Barcelona " for the transfer of Maradona. And the next day the deal was made, the clubs agreed on a transfer in the amount of 14 billion liras (about 7.6 million dollars), the largest at that time paid by football clubs for the transfer of a player, and 800 thousand to Maradona himself, who signed a contract until June 1989.
                    </p>
                    <p>On Maradona's first flight to Naples, he was greeted by a huge crowd of fans. Fans of the club lifted Maradona in their arms and carried him to the city. On July 5, the official presentation of Maradona as a player of "Napoli"took place. It took place at the San Paolo Stadium, where 70,000 spectators gathered to see the new player, who, standing in a white T-shirt and blue trousers (the official colors of Napoli), first uttered his first words in Italian: "Good evening, residents of Naples, I am happy to be with you", and then made a circle of honor, greeting the fans in all the stands: "It was an unforgettable reception and an unforgettable day for me. It was like opening a new page in my biography, and at the same time opening up a new world for me."</p>
