                    < p>Maradona made his debut for Napoli on 16 September, in an away match against Verona, which ended with a score of 1:3. In the second game of the Azzurri, Maradona hit the goal of the Sampdoria club and first of all took the ball out of the net and kissed it, which later became a tradition — this is how Maradona celebrated all his balls. On November 19, in the 84th minute of the away match with Ascoli, with the score 1:1, Maradona received his first red card in the Neapolitan club. He pushed the football player" white-black " Enrico Nicolini, who after this episode fell on the lawn, clutching his face, as a result, both players were removed from the field. In general, in the first season with Maradona, "Napoli" did not play very well: in the middle of the season, the club was even in the relegation zone from Serie A, but after a series of successful matches, the Neapolitan team straightened out the situation and took 8th place. That season, Maradona scored 14 goals, the most in a team that scored a total of 34 goals. At the end of the season, Maradona said that this was his first victory in Italy.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p><strong>1985/1986</strong></p>
                    <p>Before the start of the 1985/1986 season, Napoli began to strengthen the squad with new players, including goalkeeper Garella, Italian champion forward Giordano and midfielder Renica. The last two got into the team on the recommendation of Maradona. The club finished in 3rd place in the league, and also won the home game of Juventus (who lost in that championship only three times) thanks to a single goal by Maradona. In the same year, Maradona scored one of his most famous goals, hitting the goal of Verona, the champion of the previous season: throwing the ball into the air, Maradona shot from 40 meters, throwing the goalkeeper of the Verona team Giuliano Giuliani who went far out of the goal.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p><strong>World Cup 1986</strong></p>
                    <p>
                         <strong>Qualifying Matches</strong>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                         Maradona has not played for the Argentina national team since the 1982 World Cup. In 1983, the Argentine national team was led by Carlos Bilardo. His first step was the appointment of Diego as captain of the team, for which he personally came to Spain: "Captain of the national team. Something I've always dreamed of. To represent all the Argentine players — yes, all of them. In all the interviews, I have said that I want to finish my career as captain of the Argentina national team." Initially, the new coach of the Argentines wanted to create a team only from the players of the national championship, and call Diego only for the final games. However, he soon changed his mind and invited Maradona to a friendly match on May 10, 1985 with Paraguay, which ended in a 1-1 draw; in this game, Diego scored the only goal for the Argentines.
                    </p>
                    <p>The qualifying stage for the World Cup consisted of a group tournament. The group that included Argentina also included Venezuela, Colombia and Peru. The Argentines started with a match against Venezuela in San Cristobal, during the arrival there, one of the Venezuelans ran up to Diego and kicked him on the right knee, which caused Maradona to lie with ice on his leg all night, but then went out to the match and scored two goals, and his team won 3: 2. Then followed a series of 3 wins, which ended in a 0:1 defeat to Peru. In the last game, with the same Peru, Argentina drew 2-2 and reached the final part of the World Cup.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">Preparation</strong></p>
                    <p>The Argentines 'preparation matches for the World Cup were unsuccessful: the national team drew with Mexico, lost to France 0: 2, won with a score of 1:0 at Grasshopper, beat Israel 7: 2 and played a goalless draw with the club "Atletico Junior".</p>
                    <p>After this series of games, Bilardo decided to " put " the game of the Argentines around Maradona. This was not easy for him, Bilardo was criticized by everyone, even the president of the country, mainly for abandoning the traditions of Argentine football and closing the "door" to the national team to veterans. It came to the point that a decision was being prepared to remove Bilardo from the post of coach of the national team, and only after the intervention of Maradona, who said "if Bilardo leaves, I will also leave", the decision was canceled. To build the game around Diego Bilardo personally came to Italy, where he played Maradona: "I could send Maradona an official invitation to the national team by mail and a ticket to Mexico City, but then I would get someone else's" Italian“ Maradona, and I needed a real Argentine, who was passionate about my idea, a player of my team." During a personal conversation with Maradona, Bilardo said it would be his championship and offered him the captain's armband. He told Maradona that his place is not in the center of the field, but behind the backs of the attackers, where he can develop attacks in any direction. But all this Bilardo promised with one condition: Maradona will forget about everything, about all his hobbies and habits for 30 days for the sake of football. Bilardo even asked Maradona to swear that he would not break the regime: "Before I became captain, it was important for me to show what I can do in the game. Now the main thing is the whole team's game." Bilardo himself had full confidence in Diego: in particular, he did not take Ramon Diaz, who was in conflict with Maradona, into the national team at his request; Diego himself denied these accusations, saying that he himself asked Bilardo to take Diaz, but he refused.</p>
                    <p>Many of the national team's players, notably Daniel Passarella, the team's only 1978 world champion, were opposed to handing over the captaincy to Maradona, as were some football federation officials. Passarella himself believed that he should become the captain of the national team. It got to the point that when Daniel got an upset stomach, he did not take medication, fearing that Maradona would drug him. After the match with Atletico Junior, Maradona and Passarella had a quarrel, which resulted in mutual accusations. However, after Diego revealed that Passarella was dating the wife of one of the national team players, the entire team sided with Maradona. Passarella left the camp of the national team, although he remained in the national team's bid for the World Championship.</p>
                    <p>Maradona began training for the World Cup at the Rome Institute of Sports under the guidance of Professor Antonio del Monte, a specialist in the adaptation of athletes to the highlands, who worked with Maradona at the request of Bilardo. For 5 weeks, on Mondays, Diego went to Del Monte, where he took tests, and on the other days he conducted endurance training.</p>
                    <p>I didn't work on Maradona, I worked with Maradona. Moreover, virtually the entire faculty took part in this work. And Maradona was not a passive client, but an active, interested participant in this work, a person who seeks to learn as much as possible about himself. This is a very sensitive person, with a fine nervous activity and a sharp mind. And I would also note the obsession, dedication to my favorite business-football. Even then, it seemed to me that Maradona alone could defeat everyone. Perseverance, will, and patience had done their work. I believed in the abilities of this young man. His low center of gravity and strong legs made him a hero on the football field. The elasticity of the muscles, the power of the muscles were successfully combined with excellent reaction and extraordinary endurance. In physical terms, it can be compared to Apollo. Morally, it is a Gadfly, a person who is always ready to fight for victory. Any team needs such an athlete. His little legs are a wonderful mechanism. The Maradona looks like a car with a powerful engine and small wheels. Such a car gains acceleration earlier than others. Nature has given him the ability to quickly tense and relax his muscles, instantly change the direction of movement. While training on a soccer field in Mexico, my colleagues and I followed all his movements with a chronometer, and it was clear that his body was acting like a perfect machine. Not a single player who participated in the championship, even from the Mexicans who were used to the height, could surpass him either in skill or in sports form.</p>
                    <p>During the preparation, Maradona devoted all his time to football, did not go to parties, even avoided meetings with friends. According to the schedule, he got up at 8 and went to bed at 10, and also performed the daily captain's ritual: before going to bed, he went around his teammates and wished them good night, believing that the captain should be the soul of the team.</p>
