                    <p>The World Cup final was held, as well as the match with England, at the Azteca Stadium, at an altitude of 2350 meters above sea level. German coach Franz Beckenbauer entrusted the personal care of Maradona to Lothar Matteus, who already brought down his ward 5 times by 21 minutes, and from the penalty earned on the 5th foul, when Matteus was shown a yellow card, the score was opened: Brown scored from Batista's pass. At the beginning of the second half, the Argentines led with the score 2:0 — Valdano scored, completing the attack started by Maradona. The Germans were able to find the strength to equalize the score, twice hitting the goal of Pumpido after corners, but then in the 85th minute, Burruchaga scored, to whom Maradona gave a one-touch pass from the central circle to enter the goal. The game ended with a score of 3: 2, and in a post-match interview, Maradona said that all 11 players won this game, and that he, even with the score 2:2, was confident in the victory of his team. Immediately after the final, the Argentine fans came to Diego's mother and threw flowers at her house, dancing the tango all night under the windows and raising slogans of praise to Maradona and his family. When asked at the celebration of Argentina's victory: "Could Argentina have reached the final without Maradona," Bilardo said:<br>Maradona is an ekstraklasa player, but he is inseparable from the team team. In two aspects, Maradona is unique: in hard work and discipline. He was a constant example to his teammates. He was the first to start training and the last to finish it. He is always calm and patient on the pitch. And most importantly, the captain of the national team of Argentina was surprisingly the most disciplined player in the team. He's a great friend. His relationships with the players, coaches, and staff are impeccable. Maradona is not only a Genius of individual play. His brilliant performances on the field cannot overshadow the brilliant collective actions in the name of the team's interests. Like all great masters, Maradona has a highly developed sense of understanding of partners, a great art of passing. At the same time, even in the most tense moments of matches, when one of the players of the Argentine national team could not play because of fatigue or excitement, Maradona never showed his dissatisfaction with his teammates by a word or a gesture.</p>
                    <p>Jorge Valdano, Maradona's teammate, said: "Do you know why we won in Mexico? Because we had 20 normal players in our team and one abnormal player. This crazy guy won us the championship." Diego himself later said: "Before the start of the 1986 World Cup, the state of the team was disastrous. We didn't lose friendly matches to the strongest clubs. Bilardo gave instructions that no one understood. After his installations, someone else had to translate his words for us. Ask Valdano if you don't believe me. He went out on the pitch and didn't know what he was supposed to do. The same applies to Burruchaga. So it's not Bilardo's fault that Albiceleste won the world title. Everything was done by the players, and I myself played as I saw fit."</p>
                    <p>After returning to Buenos Aires with the national team, Diego met with the President of the country, Raul Alfonsin. The two of them went out on the balcony of the Rose House and greeted the thousands of people who filled May Square. Thanks to his game, Maradona received the "Golden Ball" as the best player of the World Cup (in 1989, the trophy itself was stolen from Diego's home in Naples). He also became the best in the number of assists and the "goal+pass" indicator.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p><strong>1986/1987</strong></p>
                    <div class="thumb tleft" style="margin: 0.5em 1.4em 1.3em 0px; width: auto; background-color: #ffffff; float: left; clear: left; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px;">
