                    <p>In February 1998, Maradona participated in an exhibition match of the club "Kareka", which was created by his former partner at "Napoli". In March 1998, having already finished his football career, Maradona received an offer to sign a contract with the club "Newells Old Boys", which was coached by his friend Sergio Batista. However, Diego refused due to financial problems with his illegitimate son. The Paraguayan Olimpia also hoped to get Maradona into their squad. Having finally finished his career as a player, Maradona took up other activities, working as a sports commentator, in particular, he commented on the matches of the 1998 World Cup for the Tele America channel, vice-president of the Commission of the Boca Juniors club and an expert in sports programs. This stage of his life was marred by health problems related to drug use. At the same time, Diego sought a cure for drug addiction, visiting clinics in Argentina and Cuba.
                    <p>
