                    <p>Due to the long stay in the hospital, Maradona gained a lot of weight: by February 2005, he weighed about 120 kg. In March of the same year, in a clinic in the city of Cartagena, he was given a brace that reduces the capacity of the stomach and eliminates part of the small intestine from the digestive process. Thanks to the operation and a strict diet, Maradona lost more than 50 kg in a few months.
                    <p>In the summer of 2005, Maradona was invited to host the talk show "Night of Ten" on Channel 13. Diego hosted the first broadcast on August 15. For this program, Maradona invited Pele. The program also featured several interviews, including Cuban leader Fidel Castro and world chess champion Anatoly Karpov, who played live chess with Diego. On November 7, the last program was held; the boxer Mike Tyson was a participant. The TV program won the 2005 Clarín Espectáculos awards as "Best Entertainment Program"; Diego received the award as "Person of the Year". In addition, Maradona participated in a dance program for the Italian RAI channel, which he refused due to long-standing problems with Italian law and the need to fly to Italy twice a week.</p>
                    <p>From June 22, 2005 to August 26, 2006, Maradona served as Vice-President of the Boca Juniors Club Board. One of his actions was lobbying for the post of head coach of the team Alfio Basile. Maradona also played in the veteran team "Boca" and charity matches Soccer Aid, which was a tournament on a variation of mini-football Showbol. In the summer of 2006, Maradona again worked as a TV commentator, commenting on the matches of the World Cup, working for the Telefe channel.</p>
                    <p>On March 17, 2007, many Argentine media reported the death of Maradona, allegedly killed in a car accident, but the information was not confirmed.</p>
                    <p>On March 28, 2007, Maradona was placed in the Guemes Clinic, due to excessive consumption of alcoholic beverages. He was diagnosed with severe intoxication. He was in the clinic until April 11. According to another version, Diego was treated for hepatitis caused by alcohol consumption. Two days after discharge, Diego had a relapse, and he was hospitalized Mother Teresa de Calcutta in the province Ezeiza with very low blood pressure and pain in the region of the stomach. He was later transferred to the Sanitarium de los Arcos in Buenos Aires, where he was diagnosed with cirrhosis of the liver. Diego stayed there until April 21, when he decided to go to the Avril psychiatric clinic. After two weeks in the clinic, he was released from the hospital on May 6. At the same time, while Diego was in Avril, rumors began to spread about his death.</p>
                    <p>In September 2008, Maradona was offered the post of representative of Inter Milan in South America, but it did not come to a real contract.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p><strong style="font-size: 14px;">At the head of the national team of Argentina</strong></p>
                    <p>Maradona expressed his desire to lead the national team of Argentina back in 1998. In 2002, he again repeated his request, while agreeing to work for free, but he was again refused.</p>
