                    <p>On October 17, 2008, after Alfio Basile resigned for personal reasons, Maradona again expressed his desire to lead the national team of Argentina. On October 28, he met with Julio Grondona, the president of the Argentine football association, where he was offered the leadership of the national team. On November 4, Maradona officially became the coach of the national team. His assistants were Carlos Bilardo, who officially held the post of technical director, Pedro Troll, Sergio Batista and Alejandro Mancuso, who were directly involved in the training of the team, as well as Fernando Signorini, who was engaged in the physical training of the team at the World Championships in 1986 and 1990. The tactics for the matches were developed by Maradona himself and Hector Enrique, Diego's partner in the 1986 national team. Maradona's first decision as coach of the national team was the appointment of Javier Mascherano as captain.</p>
