                    <p>Alfio Basile's son, Alfito, has claimed that Diego conspired against his father to remove him from the national team. According to him, Maradona met with the players of the national team of Argentina, promising them a place in the national team if he was appointed: "These meetings took place almost before every match of the national team. This senior met with the players of the national team and told them that he would be their next coach. Therefore, he is a conspirator." Maradona denied all the accusations: "Everything Alfito said is far from reality. That's not my style. My approval and my criticism of the national team has always been public. And I always wanted the national team to play well. I know Alfito, we've spoken to each other a couple of times, and I can understand that he said all these things because he was very upset that his father lost his job. A place that is very important for all of us who love football in Argentina. But there's no way I can accept what he's talking about. He disappointed me, saddened me. And it hurts, it really hurts for me." The captain of the national team, Javier Mascherano, said he did not see a plot against Basile.</p>
