                         On June 26, 2009, Diego signed a contract with the national team until 2011, before that he worked for free, according to him, he receives 139,000 euros per month (according to other sources, 110,000 dollars per month). On September 6, Argentina lost to Brazil with a score of 1: 3, and then lost to Paraguay. On October 15, after defeating Uruguay, Argentina advanced to the World Cup final. After the game, Diego said:<br>I remember well that there were those who did not believe in our team. There are many who did not believe in us. I apologize to the ladies present, but these detractors have sucked and will continue to suck. Black or white, I will never be gray in my life. Suck it-I'm talking to them the way they talked to me.
                    </p>
                    <p>Upon this statement, the FIFA commission conducted an investigation, after which Diego was disqualified for 2 months and fined 25 thousand Swiss francs. Because of his words, Diego missed the draw ceremony for the final stage of the World Cup, as the disqualification extended to official FIFA events.</p>
                    <p>In May 2010, Maradona criticized the Argentine Football Association and its president, Julio Grondona, for canceling a friendly match against the UAE national team. To this accusation, Grondona's son, Umberto, said that for his father he was "ready to trample anyone".</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p><strong>Conflict with Riquelme</strong></p>
                    <p>the match against Bolivia, from which the Argentines lost with the score 1:6, Diego aroused in Juan román Riquelme, however, in an interview with Canal 13, announced that he was leaving the national team due to personal conflicts with Maradona and different views on football; Diego said that does not understand the actions Riquelme, and that he had no conflict with the player. A few months later, a campaign was launched in the country to attract Riquelme to the national team, but Diego said that the player would not be in the national team, despite the fact that he had previously expressed his readiness to return Juan Roman to the national team if he apologized to him. Riquelme said again that the national team has no future with Maradona in charge, but wished him good luck.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                         <p>It is not true that I made statements that were offensive to Maradona. I'm not such a fool as to miss the World Cup because of some statements. This question is on a completely different plane. I repeat again that I will never work with Maradona, because I will never be able to give up my own essence.</p>
                    </blockquote>
                    <p>There is a version that the reason for the conflict was the negative attitude of the national team team to Juan Roman. And Maradona in this dispute sided with other players of the national team.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p>
                         <strong>World Cup 2010</strong>
                    </p>
                    On May 12, 2010, Maradona announced the preliminary squad of the team that will take part in the World Cup. The team's list did not include players who were regularly called up to the Albicelesta squad by previous national team coaches: Esteban Cambiasso and Javier Sanetti, saying that they are "an old story for the national team, and the team needs a new one". Diego noted that when compiling the list of players who went to the World Cup, he was extremely objective. On May 19, Maradona announced the final list of players who will take part in the World Cup. The reason for the non-recall of these players was called that they decomposed the atmosphere of camaraderie in the national team, having a great influence on the team of the national team.
                    </p>
                    <p>Maradona's former national team partner, Osvaldo Ardiles, criticized Diego for not including Cambiasso, Sanetti and Riquelme in the squad for the tournament and for not having a nominal right-back. He said that Maradona and his assistant in the national team, Carlos Bilardo, are in a state of conflict, seeking to get rid of each other. Ardiles also expressed the opinion that Maradona in making decisions about the composition and tactics for the game is guided solely by an internal voice.</p>
                    <p>Before the start of the tournament, Maradona said that he believes in this team more than in the one that won the World Cup in 1986 and expressed confidence that the players, like Diego himself, "are ready to die on the field for the sake of the Argentina national team shirt." Maradona also promised, if the national team wins, to run naked around the Obelisk in Buenos Aires. During the tournament, Maradona allowed the national team players to have sex and drink a glass of wine a day.</p>
                    <p>At the first stage of the World Cup finals, Argentina was placed in Group B, along with the teams of Nigeria, South Korea and Greece. In the first match, against Nigeria, Argentina achieved a 1-0 victory, demonstrating a good game in attack and problems in the team's defense. After the game, Diego said: "I wish I had a crystal ball, and then I could be a wizard, but I'm not a wizard, I'm just a coach. There is a lot to improve in our game to play seven matches. Of course, winning the first match at the World Cup calms you down, and you calmly continue to prepare for the next match. There is no place for fear in football. If you are afraid of something, then stay at home." In the second match of the tournament, Argentina beat South Korea 4-1; forward Gonzalo Higuain scored three goals in the game, becoming the third player in the history of the national team to score a hat-trick at the World Championships. In the third game, Argentina defeated Greece with a score of 2: 0, reaching the 1/8 finals of the tournament from the first place.</p>
                    <p>In the 1/8 final, Argentina defeated the national team of Mexico with a score of 3: 1, with the first goal of the match being scored by the Argentines from an obvious offside position. Diego himself said that his team deserved to win. One of the innovations in this match in the game of the Argentines was the inclusion in the starting line-up of Nicolas Otamendi, who replaced the right-back Jonas Gutierrez, who had previously played in all the previous matches of the national team in the tournament and acted unsuccessfully, due to a weak game in defensive actions. After the match, Clarin reported that several players of the national team are dissatisfied with the fact that they are given little playing time, but Maradona replied that relations in the national team are still excellent. On June 30, Maradona said: "I feel like I put on the national team jersey and go out on the field. It's great to coach such a group of players. I am proud to share these moments with them. They said about me that I have no idea how to train. All of a sudden, I found myself winning matches and still being the same."</p>
                    <p>On the eve of the 1/4 final, in which Argentina met Germany, Diego promised: "A minute before the quarterfinal match starts, I will tell the players that they must leave their lives on the field. That behind them — the whole country, which deserves happy moments. That it depends on them whether the whole of Argentina wakes up the next morning with a smile on its lips — or whether it will cry. In our country, people are addicted to football. Our victories can help these people overcome the most difficult moments in their lives, " Maradona also said that he has no doubts about the outcome of his team's match with Germany. In the game itself, the Argentines were defeated with a score of 0: 4 and were eliminated from the tournament. This defeat was the biggest for the national team of Argentina at the World Championships in 36 years. After the match, Maradona said: "If I retire tomorrow, I want these players to continue playing in the same style. I'm proud of my players. Whoever comes to this post will have to follow my path. I noticed that people like this kind of football, this team always strives to play and be ahead of the opponents. As for the possible departure, I have to think about it. We need to talk about this with the family, the players, the federation. There are many nuances. The result of the match against Germany does not reflect what happened on the field. The Germans used their chances, but we didn't. We gave the ball to the Germans and they took their chances well. We played well, but we didn't have enough freshness for a breakthrough." Maradona also said that he is not going to review the match with Germany, trying to evaluate the performance of the national team at the end of the entire tournament, and not a single game.</p>
                    <p>After the team's departure from the tournament, Maradona said: "I'm disappointed. It's hard to return to your homeland after this. We need to talk it over with the guys. The opponent scored, but we could not, although we had chances. We couldn't afford to lose with such a big score. I survived our relegation in the semi-finals in 1982, but I was young then. Now I'm almost 50 years old, and this is the most difficult time of my life. It's like a punch in the face. I don't have the energy to do anything else." Despite this statement, Julio Grondona asked Maradona to remain the head coach of the national team until August 11. Upon the arrival of the team in Buenos Aires, the fans who met them rewarded the players with applause, and Diego with requests to stay in the national team. On July 5, Diego said: "Yes, my time in this team is over. I gave her everything I could." On July 26, Maradona announced that he would remain in the national team only if his entire coaching staff also retained their posts. On July 27, Maradona left the post of head coach of the national team. The reason for this was the refusal of the leadership of the Argentine Football Federation to allow Diego's assistants to keep their positions, in particular, the president of the federation, Julio Grondona, demanded to dismiss Alejandro Mancuso; at the same time, the leadership of the Argentine football wanted to keep Maradona as the head coach of the national team, offering him a contract for 4 years. Grondona said he and Diego "couldn't come to a common denominator."</p>
                    <p>After leaving the national team, Diego said:</p>
                    <blockquote>
                         <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Grondona tricked me, and Bilardo betrayed me. In South Africa, we had a meeting with Grondona, a few players and other people. Grondona told me then that he was happy with my work and wanted me to stay in my post. Then he met me in Argentina and told me that seven people from my staff should leave their posts. But it was the same as if he had asked me to leave myself. They wanted to fire my people, but I didn't even discuss it. I have my own code of honor, which my father taught me. I'm not going to betray you.</p>
                    </blockquote>
                    To these accusations, Grondona replied that Maradona had misinterpreted his words.</p>
