                    <p>After leaving the Argentina national team, Maradona wanted to continue his coaching career. He expected to take the post of head coach of the Portuguese national team or the English club "Aston Villa". In September 2010, Diego wanted to return to the post of head coach of the national team, even agreeing to fire his assistants. According to a survey by Clarin and La Nacion magazines, more than 90 % of the respondents were against the return of Diego to the post of head coach of the national team.</p>
                    <p>Diego also regularly participated in charity events. On September 29, 2010, he visited Moscow, where he presented Hublot watches; there he participated in a competition, all the prize money from which, 500 thousand dollars, went to create the first Russian register of bone marrow donors to help children suffering from cancer, created by the Raisa Gorbacheva Institute of Pediatric Hematology and Transplantology: "I was happy to accept the invitation. I really wanted to win more money, because I understand how sick children need it. I am a grandfather myself, and I understand that children are our future, I really wanted to help them, I hope I managed to do something." On October 16, Diego organized a charity match between the national teams of veterans of Uruguay and Argentina, all the fees from which went to the treatment of a former player of the national team of Argentina, Fernando Caceres, who was seriously injured as a result of an armed gang attack.</p>
                    <p>In December 2010, Maradona became a candidate for the post of head coach of Blackburn Rovers, as well as the Iranian national team; however, Diego did not accept both teams. To continue his coaching career, in February 2011, Maradona signed a contract with the agency company of Jorge Mendes, dealing with the affairs of famous figures from the football world. In April 2011, Maradona became a candidate for the post of head coach of the club "San Lorenzo".</p>
