                    <p>In May, Diego reached an agreement to work for him in the Emirati club "Al-Wasl". On May 17, Maradona signed a contract with this team for two years with a salary of 3.5 million euros per season. On August 29, he made his debut as head coach of this club in a friendly match against Al-Ittihad, in which his team won 3-1. On September 22, before the match with the Emirates, Diego kicked a fan who was trying to raise a banner prepared by his granddaughter. The Argentine later apologized for his behavior. On October 8, Al-Wasl lost 0-5 to Dubai in the UAE Cup. In the same month, the coach was accused by the club's president of not being able to conduct transfer affairs; Maradona, in turn, said that he asked to strengthen the squad with new players, which was not done. He also said of his club: "Al-Wasl lacks professionalism. Some players are students, others are police officers. There are also football players who are military personnel. As a result, many players come to training tired and can't work properly. In addition, not everyone can attend the training sessions. Sometimes I have 16 and sometimes 24 players at my disposal." On December 13, Maradona was fined $ 2,700 and suspended for 3 games for a conflict after a match with the head coach of Al-Wasla's rival team, Al-Ain Club; Diego was unhappy with the way Cosmin Olaru, the head coach of the rival team, celebrated the victory over his club. Also, the Al-Wasla stadium was suspended for 2 games, after which Diego accused the UAE Football Federation of being biased against his team.</p>
                    <p>In September 2011, Maradona said that former national team player Carlos McAllister offered Diego bribes to take players to the national team. Maradona also said that Carlos had agreed with Batista and Jose Luis Brown that if they took charge of the national team, they would take the players recommended by McCallister for money. Brown said of the accusation: "My love for Maradona has turned into compassion. Diego is the best football player in the world, but you can't turn a blind eye to this. Let him produce the evidence. If this is really the case, then I will leave the country." Batista promised to apply for Maradona to the court, which he did in November.</p>
                    <p>On January 14, 2012, Maradona was hospitalized with kidney stones. The next day, he was operated on.</p>
                    <p>In February 2012, Diego said that he was persona non grata at home in Argentina due to the fact that he did not support the top sports officials in the country; he also stated that he would one day lead Boca Juniors. In the same month, he said that if Al-Wasl did not provide funds for the purchase of new players, he would leave the post of coach of the team. In March, Diego had a fight with fans from the VIP stand of Al-Wasla's rival, Al-Shebab, who insulted Maradona's girlfriend, Veronica Ojeda.</p>
                    <p>In April 2012, Diego had a conflict with the management of the club due to the fact that the players promised to him were not acquired. On July 11, 2012, the management of Al-Wasl dismissed the Argentine from the post of head coach. As it was reported on the official page of the team in the microblog on Twitter, this decision was made on Tuesday, July 10, at a meeting of the club's board. The reason for Maradona's dismissal was that during the season, Al-Wasl not only failed to win any awards, but also dropped from sixth to eighth place in the national championship, despite the fact that 12 teams play in it.</p>
                    <p>In July 2013, Maradona underwent surgery to correct age-related presbyopia.</p>
                    <p>On May 8, 2017, Maradona took charge of the Al-Fujairah club. On 27 April 2018, Maradona resigned as head coach of the Arab club after the team failed to qualify for the UAE First Division. The parties terminated the contract by mutual agreement before the end of the championship. The team would not have been able to rise above third place. However, on April 30, it was reported that the parties still agreed to extend the contract for a year. As a result, the club's management refused to cooperate with the Argentine specialist after his lawyer requested a 4-fold increase in salary.</p>
                    <p>On May 15, Maradona became the president of Dinamo Brest. The contract with the club was for three years. The Argentine had to deal with the strategic development of the club, as well as interact with all its structural divisions, including the children's academy. However, since July, Maradona has not come to Belarus.</p>
                    <p>On September 6, he headed the Mexican club "Dorados de Sinaloa". The Argentine also became the technical director of the club. This was announced on Twitter by the club, which plays in the second division of the Mexican championship. The contract is for 11 months. During this time, Diego will earn about $ 2 million. There is an automatic extension clause in the contract if the club can reach the top division.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p> <strong>Drugs</strong></p>
                    <p>According to Maradona himself, the drugs affected all of his abilities, except for his memory.</p>
                    <p>For the first time, Diego tried drugs while playing for Barcelona. He used them to make himself feel good in an unfamiliar environment: "At first I felt an emotional shock: everything around me became very bright, cheerful, entertaining. Wonderful sensations, which, unfortunately, did not last long. And then I felt the need to start it again and again, and I didn't know how to get out of it." Taking drugs was accompanied by long-term depression in Diego, as well as periods of aggression towards people close to him: "I remember with horror how my daughters came to me with a request to play with them, and I could not, because I was high. Under the eternal high. I think if it wasn't for my wife, I wouldn't be in this world right now. It's a debt I'll never pay off." At the same time, for him, drugs were not doping, did not improve his physical condition.</p>
                    <p>Addiction to drugs, according to the mother of his illegitimate child, Christiana Sinagra, was due to the fact that Maradona had a fine mental organization and a very fragile psyche. According to some, the main reason for the addiction to drugs was a close relationship with his agent, Guillermo Coppola, who was accused of drug trafficking and supplied Diego with cocaine. According to Maradona, in May 2004, he finally stopped using drugs.</p>
